    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Tear your<strong> tofu</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>torn tofu </strong>to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce</strong> (save the rest for later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up until the tofu is coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-butter-tofu-pad-thai/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated tofu</strong> to the pan and cook for 6-7 min or until golden and crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>golden tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-butter-tofu-pad-thai/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and chop your<strong> carrot[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then into thin batons</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>on diagonal</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-butter-tofu-pad-thai/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>peanut butter</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>ketjap manis</strong>, <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> and your <strong>tamarind paste </strong>in a bowl with a a squeeze of your <strong>lime juice</strong> and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>peanut butter sauce</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-butter-tofu-pad-thai/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> rice noodles</strong> to a pot and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and set aside until later</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-butter-tofu-pad-thai/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu is golden, add the<strong> carrot batons</strong> and <strong>pepper strips</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-butter-tofu-pad-thai/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened, add the <strong>drained rice noodles</strong> to the pan with your<strong> peanut butter sauce </strong>and cook for 1-2 min further</p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> peanut butter tofu pad Thai</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-butter-tofu-pad-thai/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> peanut butter tofu pad Thai</strong> and top with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
